author: Inside Edition
description: There was chaos inside the world-famous Louvre museum as panic-stricken tourists raced for the exits. Robbers disguised as construction workers pulled off what's being called the “Heist of the Century." They stole France's priceless crown jewels from inside a display case. A one-time master jewel thief says the robbers are amateurs. A former FBI agent who created the bureau's National Art Squad said he wouldn't be surprised if the robbers are captured quickly.
title: How Did The Louvre Robbers Pull Off The 'Heist Of The Century?'

author: Inside Edition
description: It's a once in a lifetime buying opportunity, if you have deep pockets. A nine and a half carat blue diamond is being auctioned off by Christie's in Geneva next month. It's called the Mellon Blue, named after its original owner, Rachel Mellon. The diamond was last seen publicly back in 2014 when it was up for auction and has since been set in a band to create a ring. Inside Edition Digital’s Mara Montalbano has more.
title: Rare 9.5 Carat 'Mellon Blue' Diamond Could Fetch Up To $30 Million At Auction

author: Inside Edition
description: The Secret Service says it discovered a "hunting stand" in a tree near West Palm Beach Airport with a "direct line of sight" to where Air Force One sits when President Donald Trump visits. The FBI is taking no chances. The FBI's Dan Bongino says the "hunting stand was dismantled and all forensic tools from digital tools to biometric tools will be applied to find out who put this up and why." Wilderness survival expert Shane Hobel showed Inside Edition how easily a hunting stand can be built.
title: Hunting Stand Found Near Trump's Air Force Landing Exit In Florida

author: Inside Edition
description: Sabrina Carpenter pulled double-duty as host and musical guest on Saturday Night Live over the weekend. Taking the stage at 30 Rock in a sparkly cocktail dress with frilly tassels. The 26-year-old kicked things off by poking fun at her sexy image. Carpenter later appeared in just a T-shirt and pink underwear for her performance for her hit song, "Man Child," which she sang into a hairbrush microphone.
title: Sabrina Carpenter Pulls Double-Duty As Host And Musical Guest On SNL

author: Inside Edition
description: What is falling like rocks into a river in Florida? Kayakers were stunned. They were monkeys, specifically rhesus macaques, and there were dozens of them. Kayaker Trenda Kitchen and her husband experienced the extraordinary encounter. They spoke with Inside Edition's Alison Hall. Zoo Miami's Ron McGill says the monkeys may be cute, but you do not want to get near them. He explains what could have made the monkeys fall from trees.
title: Is It Raining … Monkeys?

author: Inside Edition
description: Disciples of Christ First Christian Church in Katy, Texas, is grateful that two alleged thieves returned pumpkins from the parish patch after they were caught on surveillance footage putting them in the trunk of a car one night recently. The alleged thieves also covered the cost of the pumpkins that were taken and the church practice what they preached by forgiving the suspects.
title: Texas Church Forgives Alleged Pumpkin Thieves

author: Inside Edition
description: Venezuelan immigrant Tony Labrador-Sierra pleaded guilty to federal charges after posing as a 16-year-old to enroll at a high school in Perrysburg, Ohio. INSIDE EDITION spoke with fellow classmates who say Labrador-Sierra evaded detection for more than a year, joining the school's swim and soccer teams and even dating young students while enrolled. Authorities say it was all part of a plot to avoid deportation after his Visa expired more than two years ago.
title: Student Imposter: Grown Man Poses As Teen To Enroll At High School

author: Inside Edition
description: Taylor Swift's new album features a song called "The Fate of Ophelia," which, from the looks of the music video, was inspired by a painting that hangs in a museum in Germany. That piece by Friedrich Heyser is now the most popular attraction at the museum, according to the director. The painting is believed to date back to around 1900 and features the death scene of Ophelia, a character in Shakespeare's "Hamlet." Inside Edition Digital’s Mara Montalbano has more.
title: Swifties Flock To German Museum To See Painting Recreated In "Ophelia" Video

author: Inside Edition
description: ER nurse Nick Arreola says he saw the fire as he was driving home at 3 a.m. after he finished his shift in Arizona. Arreola got the family to safety, but he disappeared before they could get his name.
title: Humble Hero Reunites With Family He Saved #shorts

author: Inside Edition
description: A new medical study shows that emergency room visits by #pickleball players with eye injuries hit 1,262 last year, three times higher than just a few years ago.
title: Eye Injuries From Pickleball Are On The Rise #shorts
